questions.solution:
Each even term of the series is obtained by multiplying the previous term by 2.
2nd term = (1st term) $\times 2 = 6 \times 2 = 12$;
4th term = (3rd term) $\times 2 = 48 \times 2 = 96$;
6th term = (5th term) $\times 2 = 384 \times 2 = 768$.
\ 4th term should be 96 instead of 100.

2nd term = (1st term) $\times 3 - 4 = 10 \times 3 - 4 = 26$;
3rd term = (2nd term) $\times 3 - 4 = 26 \times 3 - 4 = 74$;
4th term = (3rd term) $\times 3 - 4 = 74 \times 3 - 4 = 218$;
5th term = (4th term) $\times 3 - 4 = 218 \times 3 - 4 = 650$.
\ 5th term must be 650 instead of 654.

2nd term = (1st term) $\times 1 + 1 = 15 \times 1 + 1 = 16$;
3rd term = (2nd term) $\times 2 + 2 = 16 \times 2 + 2 = 34$;
4th term = (3rd term) $\times 3 + 3 = 34 \times 3 + 3 = 105$;
5th term = (4th term) $\times 4 + 4 = 105 \times 4 + 4 = 424$;
6th term = (5th term) $\times 5 + 5 = 425 \times 5 + 5 = 2125$.
\ 6th term should be 2125 instead of 2124.

7th term = (8th term) $\times 2 + 1 = 20 \times 2 + 1 = 41$;
6th term = (7th term) $\times 2 + 2 = 41 \times 2 + 2 = 84$;
5th term = (6th term) $\times 2 + 3 = 84 \times 2 + 3 = 171$;
4th term = (5th term) $\times 2 + 4 = 171 \times 2 + 4 = 346$.
\ 4th term should be 346 instead of 347.

2nd term = (1st term) $+ 2^2 = 32 + 4 = 36$;
3rd term = (2nd term) $+ 3^2 = 36 + 9 = 45$;
4th term = (3rd term) $+ 4^2 = 45 + 16 = 61$;
5th term = (4th term) $+ 5^2 = 61 + 25 = 86$.
\ 3rd term should be 45 instead of 41.

$2nd term = (1st term 	imes 1 + 1^2) = 1 	imes 1 + 1^2 = 2$;
$3rd term = (2nd term 	imes 2 + 2^2) = 2 	imes 2 + 2^2 = 8$;
$4th term = (3rd term 	imes 3 + 3^2) = 8 	imes 3 + 3^2 = 33$;
$5th term = (4th term 	imes 4 + 4^2) = 33 	imes 4 + 4^2 = 148$;
$6th term = (5th term 	imes 5 + 5^2) = 148 	imes 5 + 5^2 = 765$.
$\therefore 760$ is wrong.

$2nd term = (1st term 	imes 2 + 2) = 3 	imes 2 + 2 = 8$;
$3rd term = (2nd term 	imes 2 + 4) = 8 	imes 2 + 4 = 20$;
$4th term = (3rd term 	imes 2 + 6) = 20 	imes 2 + 6 = 46$;
$5th term = (4th term 	imes 2 + 8) = 46 	imes 2 + 8 = 100$ and so on.
$\therefore 18$ is wrong.

$2nd term = (1st term - 30) 	imes  rac{1}{2} =  rac{1050 - 30}{2} = 10$;
$3rd term = (2nd term - 26) 	imes  rac{1}{2} =  rac{510 - 26}{2} = 242$;
$4th term = (3rd term - 22) 	imes  rac{1}{2} =  rac{242 - 22}{2} = 110$.
$\therefore 106$ is wrong.

$2nd term = (1st term 	imes 2 - 2) = (5 	imes 2 - 2) = 8$;
$3rd term = (2nd term 	imes 3 - 2) = (8 	imes 3 - 2) = 22$;
$4th term = (3rd term 	imes 2 - 2) = (22 	imes 2 - 2) = 42$;
$5th term = (4th term 	imes 3 - 2) = (42 	imes 3 - 2) = 124$ and so on.
$\therefore 20$ is wrong.

$2nd term = (1st term 	imes 1.5) = 2 	imes 1.5 = 3$;
$3rd term = (2nd term 	imes 2) = 3 	imes 2 = 6$;
$4th term = (3rd term 	imes 2.5) = 6 	imes 2.5 = 15$;
$5th term = (4th term 	imes 3) = 15 	imes 3 = 45$.
$\therefore 52.5$ is wrong.

$2nd term =  rac{1st term - 8}{2} =  rac{888 - 8}{2} = 440$;
$3rd term =  rac{2nd term - 8}{2} =  rac{440 - 8}{2} = 216$;
$4th term =  rac{3rd term - 8}{2} =  rac{216 - 8}{2} = 104$;
$5th term =  rac{4th term - 8}{2} =  rac{104 - 8}{2} = 48$;
$6th term =  rac{5th term - 8}{2} =  rac{48 - 8}{2} = 20$.
$\therefore 22$ is wrong.

$2nd term = (1st term 	imes 1 + 2) = (4 	imes 1 + 2) = 6$;
$3rd term = (2nd term 	imes 2 + 3) = (6 	imes 2 + 3) = 15$;
$4th term = (3rd term 	imes 3 + 4) = (15 	imes 3 + 4) = 49$;
$5th term = (4th term 	imes 4 + 5) = (49 	imes 4 + 5) = 210$ and so on.
$\therefore 5$ is wrong.
